headline: Stronger Earnings, Higher 2026 Output and Pipeline Stake Could Be A Game Changer For EQT (EQT)
summary: EQT Corporation has reported its fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results, with revenue rising to US$2,388.07 million and net income to US$677.1 million for the quarter, and full-year revenue reaching US$8.64 billion with net income of US$2.04 billion. Alongside this earnings strength, EQT raised its 2026 production outlook and increased its ownership in the Mountain Valley Pipeline to about 53%, tying higher free cash flow ambitions to expanded infrastructure control.
